'''Hi-ReS!''' or '''Handsome information - Radical entertainment Systems!''' is a London based design and [[digital marketing]] firm known for its elaborate commissioned websites.

==Background==
Hi-ReS! was founded in 1999 by German designers Alexandra Jugovic and Florian Schmitt. Their first major effort, [[soulbath.com]] attracted worldwide attention as an experimental website that questioned the use of [[banner ads]] throughout the web.<ref name=nytimes-soulbath>{{cite web|last=Mirapaul|first=Matthew|title=Compressed Data; Banner Ads Are the Target of New Banner Ads|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2000/06/12/business/compressed-data-banner-ads-are-the-target-of-new-banner-ads.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Robischon|first=Noah|title=Soulbath|url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,102209,00.html|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref><ref name=salon>{{cite web|last=Brown|first=Janelle|title=Greyscale paradise|url=http://www.salon.com/2000/03/17/soulbath/|work=[[Salon (website){{!}}Salon]]|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref> The company came to be known for its use of [[Adobe Flash|Flash]] technology to create immersive websites.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kahney|first=Leander|title=Flash Is a Gas, Gas, Gas|url=http://www.wired.com/science/discoveries/news/2000/05/35927|work=[[Wired (magazine){{!}}Wired]]|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>

The success of Soulbath subsequently brought the firm their first commercial project, when filmmaker [[Darren Aronofsky]] who reached out them about a website for his film ''[[Requiem for a Dream]]''.<ref name=nytimes_requiem>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2000/10/12/technology/moving-beyond-online-billboards.html|title=Moving Beyond Online Billboards|accessdate=17 November 2013|newspaper=The New York Times|date=12 October 2000}}</ref><ref name=design_intellect>{{cite web|title=List of 50 of the top award winning web design agencies in the world|url=http://www.design-intellect.co.uk/top_50_digital_agencies_list.html|work=Design Intellect|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>

In January 2008, Hi-ReS! was acquired by Syzygy Group, a subsidiary of British advertising company [[WPP plc|WPP]].<ref name=brandrepublic>{{cite web|title=Syzygy Group aquires interactive agency Hi-ReS!|url=http://www.brandrepublic.com/news/777349/Syzygy-Group-aquires-interactive-agency-Hi-ReS/|work=[[Brand Republic]]|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref> The following June saw their first joint project with the international website for German liqueur brand [[J<U+00E4>germeister]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Syzygy and Hi-res present new Jagermeister site|url=http://www.horizont.net/aktuell/digital/pages/protected/Syzygy-und-Hi-Res-praesentieren-neue-Jaegermeister-Site_82482.html?|work=Horizon.net|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>

Hi-ReS! owns a number of awards to its name, including a [[BAFTA]], [[Cannes Lions International Festival of Creativity|Cyber Lion]], [[Clio Awards|Clio]],<ref name=brandrepublic /> [[D&AD]], and [[Webby Awards]].<ref name=design_intellect /><ref name="FiellFiell2003">{{cite book|author1=Charlotte Fiell|author2=Peter Fiell|title=Design Graphique Au 21e Si<U+00E9>cle|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=8jY6nfAvSncC&pg=PA280|year=2003|publisher=Taschen|isbn=978-3-8228-1605-9|page=280}}</ref>

Hi-ReS! is headquartered in [[London]], [[England]], with offices in [[New York City]], [[Berlin]] and [[Hamburg]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Services|url=http://www.syzygy.net/xt_downloads/CompanyFacts_UK_July2013.pdf|work=Syzygy|accessdate=17 November 2013}}</ref>

